abstract: Homeland Security officials accused New York of jeopardizing the country’s safety by restricting access to motor vehicle databases.
snippet: Homeland Security officials accused New York of jeopardizing the country’s safety by restricting access to motor vehicle databases.
lead_paragraph: It was a sharp and sudden escalation of tension between President Trump and his former home state: a decision by Department of Homeland Security officials to bar tens of thousands of New Yorkers from enrolling in programs that allow travelers to speed through airport lines and borders.

abstract: A day after his acquittal, the president took a victory lap, and vented, in a wild White House speech.
snippet: A day after his acquittal, the president took a victory lap, and vented, in a wild White House speech.
lead_paragraph: “I’m really not a bad person,” Mr. Trump said about an hour into his speech this afternoon, his eyes searching the crowd for a response.

abstract: With impeachment behind them, House Democrats must determine how to balance their policy agenda with a determination to continue investigating President Trump.
snippet: With impeachment behind them, House Democrats must determine how to balance their policy agenda with a determination to continue investigating President Trump.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Democrats, back on their heels after President Trump’s acquittal of impeachment charges, wrestled on Thursday with a question that could determine their party’s fate in November: Now what?

headline_main: Democrats, Knocked Back by Trump’s Acquittal, Ponder Their Next Steps
headline_print_headline: Shaken by Trump’s Acquittal, Democrats Ask, What Do We Do Next?
byline_original: By Sheryl Gay Stolberg and Nicholas Fandos

abstract: We checked misleading statements that President Trump made about his trial, his political enemies and his own record.
snippet: We checked misleading statements that President Trump made about his trial, his political enemies and his own record.
lead_paragraph: President Trump celebrated his acquittal by the Senate in meandering remarks made on Thursday, when he recited a familiar litany of falsehoods and misleading assertions about the impeachment trial against him, his political enemies and his own record. Here’s a fact check.

abstract: Right now, the rewards of the economy are far too concentrated at the top.

lead_paragraph: Every Democrat running for president agrees that income inequality is one of the great problems of our time. And we all agree that the wealthy should pay more in taxes.

abstract: The president commuted the life sentence of Alice Marie Johnson. “For him to highlight me,” she says, “it makes me know he’s not only proud, he’s super proud.”
snippet: The president commuted the life sentence of Alice Marie Johnson. “For him to highlight me,” she says, “it makes me know he’s not only proud, he’s super proud.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Alice Marie Johnson was watching the Super Bowl with two of her sisters on Sunday night when she saw her own face in an advertisement amid the commercials for Doritos and Audis.

abstract: Michael Bloomberg has sworn off taking money from other people for his presidential campaign. But in private, he is courting rich Democrats, potentially posing a challenge for his moderate rivals.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg has sworn off taking money from other people for his presidential campaign. But in private, he is courting rich Democrats, potentially posing a challenge for his moderate rivals.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — In the middle of January, most Democratic presidential candidates were scrambling to raise money to keep their campaigns afloat. But at an airy gallery in downtown San Francisco, Michael R. Bloomberg gathered a group of several dozen local political donors to make a different kind of appeal.
